.TH JPEGLS 1 "2026-02-15" "JLSwift 0.1.0" "JPEG-LS Compression Tool"
.SH NAME
jpegls \- JPEG-LS command-line tool for encoding and decoding
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B jpegls
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
[\fB\-\-help\fR]
.I command
[\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B jpegls
is a command-line tool for working with JPEG-LS compressed image files. JPEG-LS (ISO/IEC 14495-1:1999 / ITU-T.87) is a lossless/near-lossless compression standard specifically designed for continuous-tone images, widely used in medical imaging (DICOM) due to its excellent compression ratio while maintaining image fidelity.
.PP
JLSwift provides a native Swift implementation optimised for Apple Silicon with hardware acceleration support, while maintaining compatibility with x86-64 systems.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B encode
Encode raw pixel data, PGM, or PPM input to JPEG-LS format.
.TP
.B decode
Decode JPEG-LS file to raw pixel data, PGM, or PPM output.
.TP
.B info
Display information about a JPEG-LS file.
.TP
.B verify
Verify JPEG-LS file integrity and validate structure.
.TP
.B batch
Process multiple JPEG-LS files in batch with parallel processing.
.TP
.B compare
Compare two image files pixel-by-pixel (JPEG-LS or PGM/PPM).
.TP
.B completion
Generate shell completion scripts for bash, zsh, or fish.
.SH ENCODE COMMAND
.B jpegls encode
[\fIoptions\fR]
.I input-file output-file
.PP
Encode an image to JPEG-LS format.
Input may be raw pixel data, PGM (P5), or PPM (P6); the format is auto-detected from the
file extension or magic bytes.
For raw input, \fB\-\-width\fR and \fB\-\-height\fR are required.
For PGM/PPM input, dimensions and component count are auto-detected from the file header.
.SS Options
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-width " " \fIpixels\fR
Image width in pixels (required for raw input; auto-detected from PGM/PPM).
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-height " " \fIpixels\fR
Image height in pixels (required for raw input; auto-detected from PGM/PPM).
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-bits\-per\-sample " " \fIbits\fR
Bits per sample, range 2-16 (default: 8; auto-detected from PGM/PPM MAXVAL).
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-components " " \fIcount\fR
Number of components: 1 for grayscale, 3 for RGB (default: 1; auto-detected from PGM/PPM).
.TP
.B \-\-near \fIvalue\fR
NEAR parameter for near-lossless encoding. 0 for lossless, 1-255 for lossy (default: 0).
.TP
.B \-\-interleave \fImode\fR
Interleaving mode: \fBnone\fR, \fBline\fR, or \fBsample\fR (default: none).
Single-component images always use 'none'.
.TP
.B \-\-colour\-transform " " \fItransform\fR (or \fB\-\-color\-transform\fR)
Colour transformation: \fBnone\fR, \fBhp1\fR, \fBhp2\fR, or \fBhp3\fR (default: none).
Both British (\-\-colour\-transform) and American (\-\-color\-transform) spellings are accepted.
.TP
.B \-\-t1 \fIvalue\fR
Custom T1 threshold parameter. All four of \-\-t1, \-\-t2, \-\-t3, and \-\-reset must be
provided together to activate custom preset parameters.
.TP
.B \-\-t2 \fIvalue\fR
Custom T2 threshold parameter (see \-\-t1).
.TP
.B \-\-t3 \fIvalue\fR
Custom T3 threshold parameter (see \-\-t1).
.TP
.B \-\-reset \fIvalue\fR
Custom RESET value for context reinitialization (see \-\-t1).
.TP
.B \-\-optimise (or \-\-optimize)
Explicitly compute and embed the default preset parameters in the output bitstream as an LSE
marker, making the file fully self-contained. Accepts both British (\-\-optimise) and
American (\-\-optimize) spellings.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-colour " (or " \-\-no\-color )
Disable ANSI colour codes in terminal output.
Accepts both British (\-\-no\-colour) and American (\-\-no\-color) spellings.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output with encoding progress.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress non-essential output (quiet mode).
.SS Examples
.TP
Encode grayscale image (lossless):
.B jpegls encode
input.raw output.jls \fB\-\-width\fR 512 \fB\-\-height\fR 512
.TP
Encode PGM image (dimensions auto-detected):
.B jpegls encode
scan.pgm output.jls
.TP
Encode PPM colour image with line interleaving:
.B jpegls encode
photo.ppm output.jls \fB\-\-interleave\fR line
.TP
Encode RGB image (raw) with sample interleaving and HP1 colour transform:
.B jpegls encode
input.raw output.jls \fB\-\-width\fR 512 \fB\-\-height\fR 512 \fB\-\-components\fR 3 \fB\-\-interleave\fR sample \fB\-\-colour\-transform\fR hp1
.TP
Near-lossless encoding (NEAR=3):
.B jpegls encode
input.raw output.jls \fB\-\-width\fR 512 \fB\-\-height\fR 512 \fB\-\-near\fR 3 \fB\-\-verbose\fR
.TP
Encode with custom preset parameters:
.B jpegls encode
input.raw output.jls \fB\-\-width\fR 512 \fB\-\-height\fR 512 \fB\-\-bits\-per\-sample\fR 8 \fB\-\-t1\fR 3 \fB\-\-t2\fR 7 \fB\-\-t3\fR 21 \fB\-\-reset\fR 64
.TP
Encode with embedded default preset (self-contained file):
.B jpegls encode
input.pgm output.jls \fB\-\-optimise\fR
.SH DECODE COMMAND
.B jpegls decode
[\fIoptions\fR]
.I input-file output-file
.PP
Decode JPEG-LS file to raw pixel data or an image file.
.SS Options
.TP
.B \-\-format \fIformat\fR
Output format: \fBraw\fR, \fBpgm\fR, \fBppm\fR, \fBpng\fR, or \fBtiff\fR (default: raw).
PGM and PPM output are supported. PNG and TIFF support is planned.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-colour " (or " \-\-no\-color )
Disable ANSI colour codes in terminal output.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output with decoding progress.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress non-essential output (quiet mode).
.SS Examples
.TP
Decode to raw format:
.B jpegls decode
input.jls output.raw
.TP
Decode to PGM (grayscale) or PPM (colour):
.B jpegls decode
input.jls output.pgm \fB\-\-format\fR pgm
.TP
Decode with verbose output:
.B jpegls decode
input.jls output.raw \fB\-\-verbose\fR
.SH INFO COMMAND
.B jpegls info
[\fIoptions\fR]
.I input-file
.PP
Display detailed information about a JPEG-LS file, including frame header, scan headers, preset parameters, and compression statistics.
.SS Options
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output in JSON format for programmatic use.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-colour " (or " \-\-no\-color )
Disable ANSI colour codes in terminal output.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Minimal output: single line with essential information only.
Format: "WIDTHxHEIGHT BITS-bit COMPONENTS-component ENCODING"
.SS Examples
.TP
Human-readable output:
.B jpegls info
image.jls
.TP
JSON output:
.B jpegls info
image.jls \fB\-\-json\fR
.TP
Quiet mode (single line):
.B jpegls info
image.jls \fB\-\-quiet\fR
.SH VERIFY COMMAND
.B jpegls verify
[\fIoptions\fR]
.I input-file
.PP
Validate JPEG-LS file structure and parameters. Checks file integrity, marker segments, header validity, and parameter consistency.
.SS Verification Steps
.IP \(bu 2
File structure validity (SOI, SOF, SOS, EOI markers)
.IP \(bu 2
Frame header parameters (dimensions, bits per sample, component count)
.IP \(bu 2
Scan header consistency with frame header
.IP \(bu 2
Preset parameter validity and threshold ordering (T1 ≤ T2 ≤ T3 ≤ MAXVAL)
.IP \(bu 2
Component ID consistency across headers
.SS Options
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output with detailed validation steps.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-colour " (or " \-\-no\-color )
Disable ANSI colour codes in terminal output.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress all output. Exit code 0 indicates success, non-zero indicates failure.
.SS Examples
.TP
Basic verification:
.B jpegls verify
image.jls
.TP
Verbose verification:
.B jpegls verify
image.jls \fB\-\-verbose\fR
.TP
Quiet mode (no output):
.B jpegls verify
image.jls \fB\-\-quiet\fR
.SH BATCH COMMAND
.B jpegls batch
[\fIoptions\fR]
.I operation input-pattern
.PP
Process multiple JPEG-LS files in parallel with encode, decode, info, or verify operations. Supports glob patterns for file matching and configurable parallelism.
.SS Arguments
.TP
.I operation
Operation to perform: \fBencode\fR, \fBdecode\fR, \fBinfo\fR, or \fBverify\fR.
.TP
.I input-pattern
Glob pattern (e.g., "*.jls", "images/*.raw") or directory path.
.SS Options
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output\-dir " " \fIdirectory\fR
Output directory for processed files (required for encode/decode).
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-width " " \fIpixels\fR
Image width in pixels (required for encode operation).
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-height " " \fIpixels\fR
Image height in pixels (required for encode operation).
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-bits\-per\-sample " " \fIbits\fR
Bits per sample, range 2-16 (default: 8, for encode operation).
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-components " " \fIcount\fR
Number of components: 1 or 3 (default: 1, for encode operation).
.TP
.B \-\-near \fIvalue\fR
NEAR parameter, 0=lossless, 1-255=lossy (default: 0, for encode operation).
.TP
.B \-\-interleave \fImode\fR
Interleave mode: \fBnone\fR, \fBline\fR, or \fBsample\fR (default: none, for encode operation).
.TP
.B \-\-colour\-transform \fItransform\fR (or \fB\-\-color\-transform\fR)
Colour transformation: \fBnone\fR, \fBhp1\fR, \fBhp2\fR, or \fBhp3\fR (default: none, for encode operation).
Both British (\-\-colour\-transform) and American (\-\-color\-transform) spellings are accepted.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-parallelism " " \fIcount\fR
Maximum number of parallel operations (default: CPU count).
.TP
.BR \-\-summarise " (or " \-\-summarize )
Always print the processing summary table, even when \-\-quiet is set.
Accepts both British (\-\-summarise) and American (\-\-summarize) spellings.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-colour " (or " \-\-no\-color )
Disable ANSI colour codes in terminal output.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Show detailed progress for each file.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress all output except errors.
.TP
.B \-\-fail\-fast
Stop processing on first error (default: continue processing all files).
.SS Examples
.TP
Get info for all .jls files:
.B jpegls batch info
"images/*.jls"
.TP
Verify all JPEG-LS files with verbose output:
.B jpegls batch verify
"/path/to/images/*.jls" \fB\-\-verbose\fR
.TP
Process with custom parallelism:
.B jpegls batch verify
"*.jls" \fB\-\-parallelism\fR 2
.TP
Stop on first error:
.B jpegls batch info
"*.jls" \fB\-\-fail\-fast\fR
.TP
Quiet batch with summary printed at the end:
.B jpegls batch verify
"*.jls" \fB\-\-quiet\fR \fB\-\-summarise\fR
.SH COMPARE COMMAND
.B jpegls compare
[\fIoptions\fR]
.I first-file second-file
.PP
Compare two image files pixel-by-pixel. Both inputs may be JPEG-LS (.jls) files or
PGM/PPM reference images. The decoded pixel data is compared component-by-component
and statistics are reported.
.PP
Exit code 0 indicates the images are identical (or every pixel is within the \fB\-\-near\fR
tolerance); exit code 1 indicates the images differ or an error occurred.
.SS Options
.TP
.B \-\-near \fIvalue\fR
Maximum per-pixel error tolerance (default: 0 for exact match).
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output comparison statistics in JSON format.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-colour " (or " \-\-no\-color )
Disable ANSI colour codes in terminal output.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output showing both image dimensions before comparing.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress all output. Use the exit code to determine the result.
.SS Statistics reported
.IP \(bu 2
\fBMax error\fR — largest per-sample absolute difference
.IP \(bu 2
\fBMean absolute error\fR — average absolute difference across all samples
.IP \(bu 2
\fBMismatch count\fR — number of samples exceeding \-\-near tolerance
.SS Examples
.TP
Exact pixel comparison of two JPEG-LS files:
.B jpegls compare
reference.jls output.jls
.TP
Near-lossless comparison (tolerance NEAR=3):
.B jpegls compare
original.jls encoded.jls \fB\-\-near\fR 3
.TP
Compare JPEG-LS against PGM reference:
.B jpegls compare
reference.pgm decoded.jls
.TP
JSON output for scripting:
.B jpegls compare
a.jls b.jls \fB\-\-json\fR
.TP
Quiet comparison (exit code only):
.B jpegls compare
a.jls b.jls \fB\-\-quiet\fR && echo "match"
.SH COMPLETION COMMAND
.B jpegls completion
.I shell
.PP
Generate shell completion scripts for bash, zsh, or fish shells. Install the generated script according to your shell's conventions to enable tab completion.
.SS Arguments
.TP
.I shell
Shell type: \fBbash\fR, \fBzsh\fR, or \fBfish\fR.
.SS Installation
.PP
.B Bash:
.IP
# System-wide installation
.br
.B sudo jpegls completion bash
> /etc/bash_completion.d/jpegls
.IP
# User installation
.br
.B jpegls completion bash
> ~/.local/share/bash-completion/completions/jpegls
.PP
.B Zsh:
.IP
# System-wide installation
.br
.B sudo jpegls completion zsh
> /usr/local/share/zsh/site-functions/_jpegls
.IP
# User installation
.br
.B mkdir -p ~/.zfunc
.br
.B jpegls completion zsh
> ~/.zfunc/_jpegls
.br
# Add to ~/.zshrc: fpath=(~/.zfunc $fpath)
.PP
.B Fish:
.IP
# User installation
.br
.B mkdir -p ~/.config/fish/completions
.br
.B jpegls completion fish
> ~/.config/fish/completions/jpegls.fish
.PP
After installation, restart your shell or source the completion file to enable tab completion.
.SS Examples
.TP
Generate bash completion:
.B jpegls completion bash
> jpegls-completion.bash
.TP
Generate zsh completion:
.B jpegls completion zsh
> _jpegls
.TP
Generate fish completion:
.B jpegls completion fish
> jpegls.fish
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-version
Display version information.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help information. Use with a command to show command-specific help.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful execution.
.TP
.B 1
Error occurred (invalid arguments, file not found, parsing error, etc.).
.SH DICOM COMPATIBILITY
JLSwift supports DICOM transfer syntaxes for medical imaging:
.TP
.B 1.2.840.10008.1.2.4.80
JPEG-LS Lossless Image Compression
.TP
.B 1.2.840.10008.1.2.4.81
JPEG-LS Lossy (Near-Lossless) Image Compression
.SH PERFORMANCE
JLSwift is optimised for Apple Silicon (M1/M2/M3) with ARM NEON/SIMD acceleration and Apple Accelerate framework integration. It also supports x86-64 systems with SSE/AVX optimisations.
.PP
The implementation includes memory optimisation features:
.IP \(bu 2
Buffer pooling for reduced allocation overhead
.IP \(bu 2
Tile-based processing for large images
.IP \(bu 2
Cache-friendly data layouts for improved performance
.SH FILES
.TP
.B /etc/bash_completion.d/jpegls
System-wide bash completion script.
.TP
.B ~/.local/share/bash-completion/completions/jpegls
User-specific bash completion script.
.TP
.B /usr/local/share/zsh/site-functions/_jpegls
System-wide zsh completion script.
.TP
.B ~/.zfunc/_jpegls
User-specific zsh completion script.
.TP
.B ~/.config/fish/completions/jpegls.fish
Fish shell completion script.
.SH STANDARDS
.B jpegls
implements the JPEG-LS standard as defined in:
.IP \(bu 2
ISO/IEC 14495-1:1999 - Lossless and near-lossless compression of continuous-tone still images
.IP \(bu 2
ITU-T Recommendation T.87 (identical to ISO/IEC 14495-1)
.SH BUGS
.IP \(bu 2
PNG and TIFF output formats for the decode command are planned but not yet implemented.
.IP \(bu 2
PNG and TIFF input formats for the encode command are planned but not yet implemented.
.PP
Report bugs at: https://github.com/Raster-Lab/JLSwift/issues
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Display information about a JPEG-LS file:
.IP
.B jpegls info
medical-image.jls
.PP
Verify file integrity:
.IP
.B jpegls verify
medical-image.jls \fB\-\-verbose\fR
.PP
Encode a grayscale medical image from raw data:
.IP
.B jpegls encode
ct-scan.raw ct-scan.jls \e
.br
  \fB\-\-width\fR 512 \fB\-\-height\fR 512 \fB\-\-bits\-per\-sample\fR 12
.PP
Encode a PGM image (dimensions auto-detected):
.IP
.B jpegls encode
ct-scan.pgm ct-scan.jls
.PP
Encode RGB image with sample interleaving:
.IP
.B jpegls encode
photo.raw photo.jls \e
.br
  \fB\-\-width\fR 1920 \fB\-\-height\fR 1080 \e
.br
  \fB\-\-components\fR 3 \fB\-\-interleave\fR sample
.PP
Near-lossless encoding with NEAR=2:
.IP
.B jpegls encode
image.raw image.jls \e
.br
  \fB\-\-width\fR 1024 \fB\-\-height\fR 768 \fB\-\-near\fR 2
.PP
Decode to PGM:
.IP
.B jpegls decode
image.jls output.pgm \fB\-\-format\fR pgm
.PP
Compare decoded output against reference:
.IP
.B jpegls compare
reference.pgm output.jls \fB\-\-verbose\fR
.PP
Batch verify all JPEG-LS files in a directory:
.IP
.B jpegls batch verify
"dicom-images/*.jls" \fB\-\-parallelism\fR 4
.PP
Batch get info with quiet mode:
.IP
.B jpegls batch info
"*.jls" \fB\-\-quiet\fR
